WEBVTT

00:23.380 --> 00:24.780
XVIII.

00:25.740 --> 00:32.520
Instead of receiving any such letter of excuse from his friend, as Elizabeth half expected Mr. Bingley to do,

00:33.000 --> 00:38.460
he was able to bring Darcy with him to Longbourn before many days had passed after Lady Catherine's visit.

00:39.200 --> 00:44.820
The gentlemen arrived early, and before Mrs. Bennet had time to tell him of their having seen his aunt,

00:45.180 --> 00:50.680
of which her daughter sat in momentary dread, Bingley, who wanted to be alone with Jane,

00:50.680 --> 00:57.440
proposed they're all walking out. It was agreed to. Mrs. Bennet was not in the habit of walking.

00:58.280 --> 01:02.720
Mary could never spare time, but the remaining five set off together.

01:03.720 --> 01:07.580
Bingley and Jane, however, soon allowed the others to outstrip them.

01:08.220 --> 01:13.580
They lagged behind, while Elizabeth, Kitty, and Darcy were to entertain each other.

01:14.400 --> 01:19.220
Very little was said by either. Kitty was too much afraid of him to talk.

01:19.220 --> 01:25.620
Elizabeth was secretly forming a desperate resolution, and perhaps he might be doing the same.

01:26.580 --> 01:30.700
They walked towards the Lucases, because Kitty wished to call upon Maria,

01:31.380 --> 01:38.640
and as Elizabeth saw no occasion for making it a general concern, when Kitty left them she went boldly on with him alone.

01:39.520 --> 01:45.600
Now was the moment for her resolution to be executed, and while her courage was high, she immediately said,

01:45.600 --> 01:53.280
Mr. Darcy, I am a very selfish creature, and for the sake of giving relief to my own feelings care not how much I may be wounding yours.

01:53.880 --> 01:58.300
I can no longer help thanking you for your unexampled kindness to my poor sister.

01:58.940 --> 02:04.000
Ever since I have known it I have been most anxious to acknowledge to you how gratefully I feel it.

02:04.520 --> 02:09.100
Were it known to the rest of the family, I should not have merely my own gratitude to express.

02:09.720 --> 02:15.180
I am sorry, exceedingly sorry, replied Darcy, in a tone of surprise and emotion,

02:15.640 --> 02:19.880
that you have ever been informed of what may, in a mistaken light, have given you uneasiness.

02:20.440 --> 02:23.160
I did not think Mrs. Gardiner was so little to be trusted.

02:24.080 --> 02:30.080
You must not blame my aunt. Lydia's thoughtlessness first betrayed to me that you had been concerned in the matter,

02:30.580 --> 02:33.800
and, of course, I could not rest till I knew the particulars.

02:33.800 --> 02:41.920
Let me thank you again and again, in the name of all my family, for that generous compassion which induced you to take so much trouble

02:41.920 --> 02:46.620
and bear so many mortifications for the sake of discovering them.

02:47.600 --> 02:52.140
If you will thank me, he replied, let it be for yourself alone.

02:52.800 --> 03:00.560
That the wish of giving happiness to you might add force to the other inducements which led me on I shall not attempt to deny.

03:00.560 --> 03:07.080
But your family owe me nothing. Much as I respect them, I believe I thought only of you.

03:08.640 --> 03:14.860
Elizabeth was too much embarrassed to say a word. After a short pause, her companion added,

03:15.740 --> 03:22.180
You are too generous to trifle with me. If your feelings are still what they were last April, tell me so at once.

03:22.680 --> 03:28.460
My affections and wishes are unchanged, but one word from you will silence me on this subject forever.

03:30.160 --> 03:37.120
Elizabeth, feeling all the more than common awkwardness and anxiety of his situation, now forced herself to speak,

03:37.660 --> 03:45.520
and immediately, though not very fluently, gave him to understand that her sentiments had undergone so material a change

03:45.520 --> 03:52.340
since the period to which she eluded, as to make her receive with gratitude and pleasure his present assurances.

03:52.340 --> 03:58.280
The happiness which this reply produced was such as he had probably never felt before,

03:58.760 --> 04:06.660
and he expressed himself on the occasion as sensibly and as warmly as a man violently in love can be supposed to do.

04:07.240 --> 04:16.460
Had Elizabeth been able to encounter his eye, she might have seen how well the expression of heartfelt delight diffused over his face became him.

04:16.460 --> 04:24.860
But though she could not look, she could listen, and he told her of feelings which, in proving of what importance she was to him,

04:25.220 --> 04:31.720
made his affection every moment more valuable. They walked on without knowing in what direction.

04:32.360 --> 04:37.720
There was too much to be thought and felt and said for attention to any other objects.

04:37.720 --> 04:44.280
She soon learnt that they were indebted for their present good understanding to the efforts of his aunt,

04:44.640 --> 04:51.160
who did call on him in her return through London, and there relate her journey to Longbourn, its motive,

04:51.560 --> 04:58.120
and the substance of her conversation with Elizabeth, dwelling emphatically on every expression of the latter which,

04:58.300 --> 05:03.780
in her ladyship's apprehension, peculiarly denoted her perverseness and assurance,

05:03.780 --> 05:11.500
in the belief that such a relation must assist her endeavours to obtain that promise from her nephew which she had refused to give.

05:12.100 --> 05:17.100
But unluckily for her ladyship, its effect had been exactly contrary-wise.

05:17.740 --> 05:23.240
It taught me to hope, said he, as I had scarcely ever allowed myself to hope before.

05:23.880 --> 05:30.300
I knew enough of your disposition to be certain that, had you been absolutely irrevocably decided against me,

05:30.300 --> 05:33.900
you would have acknowledged it to Lady Catherine, frankly and openly.

05:35.120 --> 05:37.480
Elizabeth collared and laughed as she replied,

05:38.120 --> 05:41.960
Yes, you know enough of my frankness to believe me capable of that.

05:42.460 --> 05:48.000
After abusing you so abominably to your face, I could have no scruple in abusing you to all your relations.

05:49.000 --> 05:51.460
What did you say of me that I did not deserve?

05:52.020 --> 05:56.780
For, though your accusations were ill-founded, formed on mistaken premises,

05:56.780 --> 06:01.240
my behaviour to you at the time had merited the severest reproof.

06:01.720 --> 06:05.100
It was unpardonable. I cannot think of it without abhorrence.

06:06.240 --> 06:11.160
We will not quarrel for the greater share of blame annexed to that evening, said Elizabeth.

06:11.780 --> 06:14.780
The conduct of neither, if strictly examined, will be irreproachable.

06:15.760 --> 06:18.860
But since then we have both, I hope, improved in civility.

06:19.940 --> 06:22.520
I cannot be so easily reconciled to myself.

06:22.520 --> 06:28.840
The recollection of what I then said, of my conduct, my manners, my expressions during the whole of it,

06:28.840 --> 06:32.960
is now, and has been many months, inexpressibly painful to me.

06:33.580 --> 06:36.480
Your reproof so well applied, I shall never forget.

06:37.300 --> 06:39.900
Had you behaved in a more gentleman-like manner?

06:40.580 --> 06:46.420
Those were your words. You know not, you can scarcely conceive how they have tortured me,

06:46.840 --> 06:51.360
though it was some time, I confess, before I was reasonable enough to allow their justice.

06:52.180 --> 06:56.460
I was certainly very far from expecting them to make so strong an impression.

06:57.000 --> 07:00.420
I had not the smallest idea of their being ever felt in such a way.

07:01.580 --> 07:07.140
I can easily believe it. You thought me then devoid of every proper feeling. I am sure you did.

07:07.780 --> 07:10.460
The turn of your countenance I shall never forget,

07:10.780 --> 07:15.580
as you said that I could not have addressed you in any possible way that would induce you to accept me.

07:16.460 --> 07:20.540
Oh, do not repeat what I then said. These recollections will not do at all.

07:20.540 --> 07:24.320
I assure you that I have long been most heartily ashamed of it.

07:25.380 --> 07:26.660
Darcy mentioned his letter.

07:27.420 --> 07:31.020
Did it, said he, did it soon make you think better of me?

07:31.460 --> 07:34.260
Did you, on reading it, give any credit to its contents?

07:35.120 --> 07:37.800
She explained what its effect on her had been,

07:38.120 --> 07:41.640
and how gradually all her former prejudices had been removed.

07:42.460 --> 07:47.440
I knew, said he, that what I wrote must give you pain, but it was necessary.

07:47.440 --> 07:49.680
I hope you have destroyed the letter.

07:50.180 --> 07:52.600
There was one part especially, the opening of it,

07:52.720 --> 07:55.240
which I should dread your having the power of reading again.

07:55.920 --> 07:59.560
I can remember some expressions which might justly make you hate me.

08:00.620 --> 08:05.180
The letter shall certainly be burnt, if you believe it essential to the preservation of my regard.

08:05.760 --> 08:10.380
But, though we have both reason to think my opinions not entirely unalterable,

08:10.900 --> 08:14.740
they are not, I hope, quite so easily changed as that implies.

08:15.740 --> 08:20.860
When I wrote that letter, replied Darcy, I believed myself perfectly calm and cool,

08:21.000 --> 08:25.340
but I am since convinced that it was written in a dreadful bitterness of spirit.

08:26.480 --> 08:29.960
The letter perhaps began in bitterness, but it did not end so.

08:30.680 --> 08:32.420
The adieu is charity itself.

08:33.060 --> 08:34.260
But think no more of the letter.

08:34.460 --> 08:37.880
The feelings of the person who wrote, and the person who received it,

08:38.220 --> 08:41.000
are now so widely different from what they were then,

08:41.000 --> 08:44.660
that every unpleasant circumstance attending it ought to be forgotten.

08:45.260 --> 08:47.120
You must learn some of my philosophy.

08:47.660 --> 08:50.600
Think only of the past, as its remembrance gives you pleasure.

08:51.920 --> 08:55.020
I cannot give you credit for any philosophy of the kind.

08:55.660 --> 08:59.420
Your retrospections must be so totally void of reproach

08:59.420 --> 09:02.460
that the contentment arising from them is not of philosophy,

09:03.060 --> 09:05.360
but, what is much better, of innocence.

09:05.900 --> 09:07.580
But with me it is not so.

09:07.580 --> 09:12.740
Painful recollections will intrude, which cannot, which ought not, to be repelled.

09:13.460 --> 09:17.700
I have been a selfish being all my life, in practice, though not in principle.

09:18.480 --> 09:22.780
As a child I was taught what was right, but I was not taught to correct my temper.

09:23.480 --> 09:27.700
I was given good principles, but left to follow them in pride and conceit.

09:28.200 --> 09:31.680
Unfortunately, an only son, for many years an only child,

09:32.040 --> 09:35.800
I was spoiled by my parents, who, though good themselves,

09:35.800 --> 09:39.800
my father particularly, all that was benevolent and amiable,

09:40.720 --> 09:44.560
allowed, encouraged, almost taught me to be selfish and overbearing,

09:44.920 --> 09:47.420
to care for none beyond my own family circle,

09:47.920 --> 09:50.160
to think meanly of all the rest of the world,

09:50.660 --> 09:54.640
to wish at least to think meanly of their sense and worth compared with my own.

09:55.300 --> 10:00.880
Such I was from eight to eight and twenty, and such I might still have been, but for you.

10:01.280 --> 10:04.940
Dearest, loveliest Elizabeth, what do I not owe you?

10:04.940 --> 10:10.040
You taught me a lesson, hard indeed at first, but most advantageous.

10:10.400 --> 10:15.180
By you I was properly humbled. I came to you without a doubt of my reception.

10:15.880 --> 10:21.000
You showed me how insufficient were all my pretensions to please a woman worthy of being pleased.

10:22.020 --> 10:24.280
Had you then persuaded yourself that I should?

10:25.340 --> 10:28.400
Indeed I had. What will you think of my vanity?

10:28.940 --> 10:32.120
I believed you to be wishing, expecting my addresses.

10:32.920 --> 10:37.540
My manners must have been in fault, but not intentionally, I assure you.

10:37.860 --> 10:42.140
I never meant to deceive you, but my spirits might often lead me wrong.

10:42.840 --> 10:44.960
How you must have hated me after that evening.

10:46.000 --> 10:51.900
Hate you? I was angry perhaps at first, but my anger soon began to take a proper direction.

10:52.980 --> 10:57.000
I am almost afraid of asking what you thought of me when we met at Pemberley.

10:57.380 --> 10:58.760
You blamed me for coming?

10:59.380 --> 11:02.260
No, indeed, I felt nothing but surprise.

11:03.300 --> 11:07.200
Your surprise could not be greater than mine in being noticed by you.

11:07.700 --> 11:11.260
My conscience told me that I deserved no extraordinary politeness,

11:11.640 --> 11:14.760
and I confess that I did not expect to receive more than my due.

11:15.800 --> 11:21.300
My object then, replied Darcy, was to show you, by every civility in my power,

11:21.680 --> 11:24.380
that I was not so mean as to resent the past,

11:24.380 --> 11:28.940
and I hoped to obtain your forgiveness, to lessen your ill opinion,

11:29.220 --> 11:32.380
by letting you see that your reproofs had been attended to.

11:32.960 --> 11:36.500
How soon any other wishes introduced themselves I can hardly tell,

11:37.040 --> 11:40.340
but I believe in about half an hour after I had seen you.

11:41.160 --> 11:44.420
He then told her of Georgiana's delight in her acquaintance,

11:44.560 --> 11:47.260
and of her disappointment at its sudden interruption,

11:47.780 --> 11:50.580
which naturally leading to the cause of that interruption,

11:50.580 --> 11:54.740
she soon learned that his resolution of following her from Derbyshire

11:54.740 --> 11:59.360
in quest of her sister had been formed before he quitted the inn,

11:59.620 --> 12:04.540
and that his gravity and thoughtfulness there had arisen from no other struggles

12:04.540 --> 12:06.980
than what such a purpose must comprehend.

12:08.220 --> 12:10.420
She expressed her gratitude again,

12:10.700 --> 12:14.420
but it was too painful a subject to each to be dwelt on farther.

12:15.320 --> 12:18.380
After walking several miles in a leisurely manner,

12:18.380 --> 12:20.760
and too busy to know anything about it,

12:21.000 --> 12:23.320
they found at last, on examining their watches,

12:23.780 --> 12:25.340
that it was time to be at home.

12:26.120 --> 12:28.500
What would become of Mr. Bingley and Jane

12:28.500 --> 12:32.160
was a wonder which introduced the discussion of their affairs.

12:33.180 --> 12:35.000
Darcy was delighted with their engagement.

12:35.300 --> 12:38.020
His friend had given him the earliest information of it.

12:38.600 --> 12:42.200
I must ask whether you were surprised, said Elizabeth.

12:42.740 --> 12:46.200
Not at all. When I went away I felt that it would soon happen.

12:46.740 --> 12:50.680
That is to say you had given your permission. I guessed as much.

12:51.520 --> 12:53.220
And though he exclaimed at the term,

12:53.300 --> 12:55.820
she found that it had been pretty much the case.

12:56.700 --> 12:59.800
On the evening before my going to London, said he,

13:00.080 --> 13:03.620
I made a confession to him which I believe I ought to have made long ago.

13:04.140 --> 13:07.360
I told him of all that had occurred to make my former interference

13:07.780 --> 13:10.300
in his affairs absurd and impertinent.

13:11.020 --> 13:14.480
His surprise was great. He had never had the slightest suspicion.

13:14.480 --> 13:18.180
I told him moreover that I believed myself mistaken

13:18.180 --> 13:22.100
in supposing, as I had done, that your sister was indifferent to him.

13:22.440 --> 13:26.320
And as I could easily perceive that his attachment to her was unabated,

13:26.720 --> 13:28.940
I felt no doubt of their happiness together.

13:30.060 --> 13:34.240
Elizabeth could not help smiling at his easy manner of directing his friend.

13:35.100 --> 13:38.200
Did you speak from your own observation, said she,

13:38.480 --> 13:40.680
when you told him that my sister loved him,

13:40.920 --> 13:43.240
or merely from my information last spring?

13:43.240 --> 13:47.340
From the former. I had narrowly observed her

13:47.340 --> 13:49.840
during the two visits which I had lately made here,

13:50.200 --> 13:51.900
and I was convinced of her affection.

13:53.040 --> 13:57.260
And your assurance of it, I suppose, carried immediate conviction to him.

13:58.000 --> 14:01.460
It did. Bingley is most unaffectedly modest.

14:02.020 --> 14:06.960
His diffidence had prevented his depending on his own judgment in so anxious a case,

14:07.340 --> 14:10.320
but his reliance on mine made everything easy.

14:10.320 --> 14:16.240
I was obliged to confess one thing, which for a time, and not unjustly, offended him.

14:16.660 --> 14:21.620
I could not allow myself to conceal that your sister had been in town three months last winter,

14:22.080 --> 14:24.880
that I had known it and purposely kept it from him.

14:25.380 --> 14:29.280
He was angry, but his anger I am persuaded lest it no longer

14:29.280 --> 14:32.160
than he remained in any doubt of your sister's sentiments.

14:32.960 --> 14:35.040
He has heartily forgiven me now.

14:36.240 --> 14:40.740
Elizabeth longed to observe that Mr. Bingley had been a most delightful friend,

14:41.180 --> 14:44.060
so easily guided that his worth was invaluable.

14:44.740 --> 14:45.960
But she checked herself.

14:46.600 --> 14:49.660
She remembered that he had yet to learn to be laughed at,

14:49.820 --> 14:51.760
and it was rather too early to begin.

14:52.880 --> 14:54.900
In anticipating the happiness of Bingley,

14:55.160 --> 14:58.060
which of course was to be inferior only to his own,

14:58.400 --> 15:01.240
he continued the conversation till they reached the house.

15:01.840 --> 15:03.900
In the hall they parted.

15:03.900 --> 15:06.180
End of chapter 58

